# Changelog / Release notes

The information about Unicis Platform releases and changes is listed in order below.

## [UX/UI — Direction B Design System] 2026-06-09

*Release date: 2026-06-09*

A full UX/UI overhaul across all modules introducing the Direction B design language — a calm, consistent visual system optimised for compliance and security professionals (CISO, DPO, Engineers, DevSecOps, HR, C-level).

- Design System Foundation
  - Introduced Direction B design token set: card shell (`bg-white dark:bg-slate-800 border border-slate-200 dark:border-slate-700 rounded-xl`), panel header, table header typography, tab bar, and hover states — applied consistently across every module surface
  - Standardised table header typography: `text-[11px] font-medium text-slate-500 dark:text-slate-400 uppercase tracking-wide` applied to All Tasks, RPA, TIA, PIA, CSC, and Risk Management tables
  - All module Create buttons migrated from DaisyUI `color="primary"` to Shadcn `<Button variant="default">` (RPA, TIA, PIA, Risk Management, IAP Admin)
  - `ModuleEmptyState` shared component CTA button migrated from DaisyUI `btn btn-primary btn-sm` to Shadcn `<Button size="sm">`
  - `ModuleBadge` rewritten as a pure Tailwind component — removes DaisyUI dependency, preserves per-module colours (RPA red, TIA blue, PIA amber, RM green, CSC slate)

- Dashboard
  - KPI row: task counts, overdue indicator, completion rate, compliance score with sparkline trend line
  - Task Overview by Module matrix: module column now uses coloured `ModuleBadge` badges (identical to All Tasks view) instead of dot + plain text
  - Action Required / Needs Attention panel
  - GRC AI Assistant upgrade gate
  - URL-encoded filter state for bookmark/share support

- All Tasks
  - Direction B card wrapper and table header typography applied to `TaskListView`
  - Module badges (`ModuleBadge`) rendered inline with task title showing which modules (RPA, TIA, PIA, RM, CSC) each task is associated with
  - Global search across task title, number, status, priority, and module fields

- Module Headings & Record Counts
  - Every module dashboard now shows a `<h1>` page heading with a pill displaying the active record count: RPA, TIA, PIA, Risk Management, IAP

- Comments (Direction B Redesign)
  - Single-column layout: avatar + header on one row, content below
  - Hover-reveal Edit/Delete actions (opacity transition, no layout shift)
  - `CommentAvatar`: `h-7 w-7 rounded-full`, slate border tokens, fixed `<label>` → `<div>` semantic error
  - `CommentHeader`: name `text-[13px] font-semibold`, date `text-[11px] text-slate-400` inline with `·` separator
  - Compose area: `focus-within:border-slate-400` ring transition

- RPA Module
  - Direction B card wrapper on `RpaTable`
  - Direction B table header typography

- TIA Module
  - **Bug fix**: Legal Analysis column was incorrectly rendering `DataExporter` (duplicate of column 2) — now correctly renders `LawImporterCountry` from `procedure[0]`
  - Direction B table header typography

- PIA Module
  - **Bug fix**: First column header labelled `t('rpa')` — corrected to `t('title')`
  - Direction B table header typography

- Cybersecurity Controls (CSC)
  - **Bug fix**: Dark mode tab text used `dark:text-slate-200` unconditionally — all inactive tabs appeared selected in dark mode; fixed to `dark:hover:text-slate-200`
  - `CscChartsLayout` Panel component updated to Direction B card tokens
  - `CscPanel` now wraps `StatusesTable` + `SectionRail` inside a single Direction B card — both surfaces share one visual container
  - `StatusesTable` header cells reduced from `px-6 py-3` to `px-3 py-2` with Direction B typography
  - Removed debug `console.log('cscTranslations', ...)` from `pages/teams/[slug]/csc.tsx`

- Risk Management (RM)
  - Full table rewrite: removed `VerticalHeader` (rotate-180 + `writing-mode: vertical-rl`) which forced users to tilt their head to read 14 column headers
  - New two-row grouped header design: section group labels (Raw Risk / Treatment / Target Risk / Current Risk) above individual column labels
  - **Bug fix**: `<tr key={idx}>` changed to `<tr key={task.id}>` for stable React reconciliation
  - **Bug fix**: Asset Owner column showed "Not found" — `membersById[userId]` (invalid Map bracket access) replaced with `membersById.get(userId)` (correct Map API)
  - Risk colour cells now use a static class lookup table, removing dynamic Tailwind class names that broke JIT compilation

- Interactive Awareness Training (IAP)
  - Added completion summary banner above the course grid: progress bar, completion percentage, Total / Completed / In-Progress stat chips
  - Admin page: removed unnecessary `<div className="mx-1.5 my-0">` wrappers around Create buttons

- Audit Logs
  - `AuditTimeline` generic component introduced and wired to all modules (RPA, TIA, PIA, CSC, RM)

## [Tasks] 2026-05-31

Release date: 2025-05-31

- New Features
  - Added task import templates that generate tasks from enabled CSC framework controls
  - Added a dialog to set a CSC control status after linking a task to an unknown-status control
  - Kanban tasks board
  - Recurring tasks
  - Import/Export for RoPA/TIA/PIA/RM
- Enhancements
  - Added bulk and per-control linking of tasks to mapped CSC controls across enabled frameworks, including status propagation from the source control
  - Emojis for comments
  - Prioritizations for tasks
  - Import/Export supports OpenDocument standard
  - Audit logs for tasks changes
  - Notification team identifier
  - PIA/RM links for dashboard matrix
  - Links added for RoPA/TIA/PIA/RM steps
- Fixes
  - Task attachments visible only on overview tab
  - Hid the CSC matrix mapping view from the task-level CSC issue panel

## [Validation, Permissions & Audit Log Fixes] 2026-05-12

*Release date: 2026-05-12*

- Improvements
  - User Registration
    - Added Zod validation for user registration forms
    - Improved input validation and error handling consistency
- Fixes
  - SAML
    - Fixed React version compatibility issue on the SAML page
  - Settings & Permissions
    - Fixed OWNER role having incorrectly restricted permissions in Settings
  - Training
    - Fixed Training start button label capitalization
  - API Documentation
    - Fixed Notification API documentation specification inconsistencies
  - Audit Logs
    - Fixed Audit Log service
    - Improved Audit Log service reliability and stability

## [Notification + REST API Docs] 2026-03-31

*Release date: 2026-03-31*

- Notifications:
  - In-app notification bell with real-time unread count
  - Email and web push notification channels
  - Per-user notification preferences
- REST API:
  - OpenAPI 3.0 specification (Swagger UI available at /api-docs)
  - API Key Bearer Token authentication — generate keys in Team Settings
  - Consistent JSON response envelope: { "data": ..., "error": null }
  - Endpoints covering Tasks, Cybersecurity Controls (CSC), Risk Management, PIA, RPA, TIA, API Keys, and AI Chatbot
- New Frameworks:
  - Added OWASP ASVS v5 — Application Security Verification Standard
  - Added PCI DSS v4.0.1 — Payment Card Industry Data Security Standard
  - Added ISO/IEC 42001 — AI Management System Standard
- Tasks:
  - Added task.due_date webhook event — triggers when a due date is set or changed on a task
  - Notifications now cover: Task due, Task created, Task updated, Task commented, Task deleted, and File uploaded — each configurable per channel (in-app, email, push)
- Security:
  - Bearer token verification: expiration checks and team-scoped access
  - SBOM (Software Bill of Materials) generated and published
  - Bearer SAST scan — vulnerabilities reviewed and resolved
  - npm audit fix applied
- Fixes:
  - Fixed Team Create button missing
  - Fixed Billing modal: country (en) key returning object instead of string

## [Controls Mapping] 2026-03-07

*Release date: 2026-03-07*

- New Features
  - Tasks
    - Added export functionality for Tasks in HTML, PDF, Excel, and CSV formats.
    - Added bulk import capability and task template support via Excel or CSV files.
  - Cybersecurity Management System
    - Added export functionality for the Statement of Applicability (SoA) in HTML, PDF, and Excel formats.
    - Introduced Controls Mapping across multiple frameworks and standards, including:
      - Visibility of the number of mapped controls
      - Detailed view of relationships between mapped controls
      - Display of Tasks linked to mapped controls
    - Added Controls Mapping Matrix to visualize the mapping status between different frameworks and standards.

- Security
  - Updated Prisma and Next.js to their latest stable versions.

- Fixes
  - Fixed issues affecting Cybersecurity controls selection.
  - Updated platform pricing display.
  - Fixed issues in the Risk Management dashboard.


## [Internationalization] 2026-02-05

*Release date: 2026-02-05*

- New Features 
  - Added localization support: The platform is now available in French, German, and Spanish alongside the default English. Check the status on the [translation platform](https://locales.unicis.tech/weblate/projects/unicis-platform/).
  - Added theme toggle on login page
  - Added copy action for API keys
  - Added ENV variable for AI custom integration with different models and providers
- Enhancements 
  - Improved chart labels and readability in localized views
  - Improved responsiveness across key pages and forms
  - Refreshed UI consistency in navigation, cards, and tables
  - The minimum Risk value can be set to 0%
  - Better behavior of multiselector
  - Improved 404 page
  - Updated features plan: AI Chatbot now available for Premium and Ultimate
- Fixes 
  - Fixed visual issues in dark theme and legacy browser cases
  - Fixed navigation and layout issues on mobile
  - Fixed issues in selectors and filtering behavior
  - Fixed description editor in Interactive Awareness Training module
  - Fixed task comments behavior
  - Vulnerability fixed: 
      - HIGH: Unsanitized user input in HTTP response (XSS) [CWE-79](https://docs.bearer.com/reference/rules/javascript_express_cross_site_scripting)
      - Unsanitized user input in dynamic HTML insertion (XSS) [CWE-79](https://docs.bearer.com/reference/rules/javascript_lang_dangerous_insert_html)
  - Library updates `npm audit fix`

## [Feature] 2025-10-24

*Release date: 2025-10-24*

- New Features 
  - Added [SOC 2 compliance](/frameworks/soc) framework
  - Added [C5:2020 compliance](/frameworks/c5) framework
  - Introduced [multiple framework support](/docs/platform/using/settings#multi-framework-selection) for improved flexibility
- Enhancements 
  - Improved permission schema for better access control management
  - Added [Markdown](https://daringfireball.net/projects/markdown/syntax) shortcuts for task comments and descriptions
  - Introduced "[Resend](https://resend.com/) verification email" button for easier user onboarding
  - Added "Copy" [button for invitation links](/docs/platform/using/settings#members)
  - Enhanced chart readability
  - Improved mobile view layouts for better responsiveness
  - Docker hub repository for [Unicis Platform](https://hub.docker.com/r/stepcellwolf/unicis-platform-ce)
- Access & Security 
  - [Audit logs](/docs/platform/using/settings#audit-logs) are now available exclusively for Ultimate plan users
  - Improve security with introducing CI/CD pipeline by adding [Bearer](https://github.com/Bearer/bearer) code security scanning tool (SAST) to discover, filter and prioritize security and privacy risk in Unicis Platform
- Fixes/Bugs
  - Email service reliability improvements with introducing [Resend](https://resend.com/) intergation for email delivery


